<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 753
                    The Under Secretary of the Navy (
                        Gates
                    ) to the Assistant Chief of Staff for Plans to the
                        Commander in Chief, United States Fleet (
                        Gardner
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d753</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">753</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="753" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 753<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GAL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gates</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Chief of Staff for Plans to the
                        Commander in Chief, United States Fleet</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GRAMB1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gardner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-21">21 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_ComNavEu1">ComNavEu</gloss> passes action UnderSeeNavs 212100
                    to <gloss target="#t_CominCh1">CominCh</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CNO1">CNO</gloss> for <persName corresp="#p_GRAMB1">Rear Admiral Matthias B.
                        Gardner</persName>.</p>
                <p>Please see Joint Chiefs memorandum to State <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                    Navy Coordinating Committee 17 July 1945<note n="1" xml:id="d753fn1">
                        <ref target="#d751">Document No. 751</ref>.</note> original of which was
                    delivered to <persName corresp="#p_GCHA1">Colonel Harrison Gerhardt</persName>
                    at <gloss target="#t_Terminal1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terminal</hi>
                    </gloss> on 17 July 1945. …<note n="2" xml:id="d753fn2">For the sentence omitted
                        here, see <ref target="#d1368">document No. 1368</ref>.</note> We<note n="3" xml:id="d753fn3">i. e., <persName corresp="#p_GAL1">Gates</persName> and
                        Secretary of the Navy <persName corresp="#p_FJ1">James
                        Forrestal</persName>.</note> feel you should vigorously support treatment of
                    Kiel [Canal] recommended by Joint Chiefs if question of Kiel cannot be
                    avoided.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
